<p>Our recommended setup for maximum flexibility:</p>

<h3>Primary: Digital Lock</h3>
<ul>
<li>Used for 90% of guests</li>
<li>Self check-in enabled</li>
<li>Remote monitoring</li>
</ul>

<h3>Backup: Physical Key in Keybox</h3>
<ul>
<li>For technology-failing situations</li>
<li>For guests who insist on physical keys</li>
<li>Emergency access for cleaning team</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Cost:</strong> RM800-1,000 (digital) + RM150 (keybox) = RM950-1,150 total</p>

<p><strong>Benefit:</strong> 100% guest satisfaction, no lockouts, maximum flexibility.</p>

<h2>Key Security Best Practices</h2>

<h3>For Digital Locks:</h3>

<ul>
<li><strong>Change codes after every guest</strong> (automatic on most systems)</li>
<li><strong>Monitor battery levels</strong> monthly (replace at 20%)</li>
<li><strong>Keep backup physical key</strong> in secure location</li>
<li><strong>Update firmware</strong> when available</li>
<li><strong>Use unique codes</strong> (don't reuse previous codes)</li>
</ul>

<h3>For Physical Keys:</h3>

<ul>
<li><strong>Use keyboxes with changeable codes</strong></li>
<li><strong>Log key handovers</strong> (tracking system)</li>
<li><strong>Rekey annually</strong> or after lost keys</li>
<li><strong>Never label keys</strong> with unit numbers</li>
<li><strong>Consider restricted keys</strong> (cannot be copied)</li>
</ul>

